9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 638, L.D. 978, “An Act to Increase
10 General Assistance Reimbursement for Municipalities and Indian Tribes”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §4308, sub-§1-A, as enacted by PL 2011, c. 655, Pt. R, §2, is
14 amended to read:
15 1-A. Limit on housing assistance. Except as provided in subsections 1‑B and 2,
16 housing assistance provided pursuant to this chapter is limited to a maximum of 9 months
17 during the period from July 1, 2012 to June 30, 2013. Beginning July 1, 2025, except as
18 provided in subsections 1‑B and 2, housing assistance provided pursuant to this chapter is
19 limited to a maximum of 12 months in a 36-month period.
20 Sec. 2. 22 MRSA §4311, sub-§1, as amended by PL 2015, c. 267, Pt. SSSS, §1, is
21 further amended to read:
22 1. Departmental reimbursement. When a municipality incurs net general assistance
23 costs in any fiscal year prior to July 1, 2015 in excess of .0003 of that municipality's most
24 recent state valuation relative to the state fiscal year for which reimbursement is being
25 issued, as determined by the State Tax Assessor in the statement filed as provided in Title
26 36, section 381, the Department of Health and Human Services shall reimburse the
27 municipality for 90% of the amount in excess of these expenditures when the department
28 finds that the municipality has been in compliance with all requirements of this chapter. If
29 a municipality elects to determine need without consideration of funds distributed from any
30 municipally-controlled municipally controlled trust fund that must otherwise be considered
31 for purposes of this chapter, the department shall reimburse the municipality for 66 2/3%
32 of the amount in excess of such expenditures when the department finds that the
33 municipality has otherwise been in compliance with all requirements of this chapter.
34 The department shall reimburse each municipality and each Indian tribe 70% of the direct
35 costs incurred by that municipality or tribe on or after July 1, 2015 and before July 1, 2025
