3 The department shall reimburse each municipality and Indian tribe as follows:
4 A. Beginning July 1, 2025, the department shall reimburse each municipality and each
5 Indian tribe 75% of the direct costs incurred by that municipality or tribe for costs
6 incurred on or after July 1, 2025 and before July 1, 2027; and
7 B. Beginning July 1, 2027, the department shall reimburse each municipality and each
8 Indian tribe 80% of the direct costs incurred by that municipality or tribe for costs
9 incurred on or after July 1, 2027.
10 For the purposes of this subsection, "Indian tribe" has the same meaning as in section 411,
11 subsection 8-A.
12 Sec. 3. 22 MRSA §4323, sub-§6, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 575, §6, is repealed.
13 Sec. 4. 22 MRSA §4327, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 575, §7, is amended to read:
14 §4327. Reporting
15 The department shall use municipal reports, data from the statewide online database
16 required under section 4323, subsection 6 and other metrics to generate a general assistance
17 report to be submitted to the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction
18 over general assistance matters no later than January 30, 2026 and no later than January
19 30th of each odd-numbered calendar year thereafter. The initial report must include
20 recommendations regarding a potential extension of the general assistance eligibility period
21 beyond the 30-day limit established in section 4310, subsection 4. All reports must include
22 metrics for: the number of individuals and families who received funds; the basic
23 necessities for which those funds were provided; the length of time those funds were
24 received; which municipalities accessed technical assistance and the number of times that
25 technical assistance was requested, including instances outside of normal business hours;
26 the type of technical assistance municipalities required; the number of calls to the
27 department's general assistance hotline; and the number and content of complaints received
28 and additional metrics as determined necessary by the department. The report must also
29 include data illustrating municipal poverty levels, or regional or county poverty data when
30 municipal-level poverty data is unavailable, and data regarding the use of other public
31 benefit programs such as the Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program and the
32 Temporary Assistance for Needy Families program in each municipality.
33 Sec. 5. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
34 allocations are made.
