11 '
2 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
3 number to read consecutively.
4 SUMMARY
55 This amendment replaces the bill. The amendment provides that, beginning July 1,
66 2025, housing assistance is limited to a maximum of 12 months in a 36-month period.
77 Current law provides that individuals eligible for emergency general assistance, including
88 individuals experiencing or facing homelessness, and certain individuals with severe and
99 persistent mental or physical conditions are exempt from this limitation. The amendment
1100 also requires the Department of Health and Human Services to reimburse municipalities
1111 and Indian tribes 75% of the direct costs incurred by that municipality or tribe for costs
1122 incurred on or after July 1, 2025 and before July 1, 2027 and that beginning July 1, 2027,
1133 the department must reimburse each municipality and each Indian tribe 80% of the direct
1144 costs incurred by that municipality or tribe for costs incurred on or after July 1, 2027.
1155 Finally, the amendment removes the requirement that the department, beginning July 1,
1166 2025, provide overseers access to an Internet-based, real-time database containing the
1177 information necessary to properly determine eligibility of an applicant for general
1188 assistance.
